versos.title: Inside people's heads -01
versos.description: This is a photograph of "Peregrinus", an outdoor performance in Tehran, Iran, by KTO-Theater - a Polish theater group - written by T. S. Eliot.  I was moving, running, jumping, and even lying on the floor while photographing this performance. It's a very exciting and different experience, unlike shooting in a theater where you have to sit still and shoot in silence. Of course, the contrast of the light also created a special attraction.  The fact is that I did not pay attention to the story at all. I paid more attention to the reaction of the audience. I was interested in the frames where the actors and the audience were together.  When you look at these big heads, do you know what the people looking at them are thinking?

versos.title: 202305-HYDRA
versos.description: At first glance, this image may seem unremarkable. A friend and I had just enjoyed a beautiful day on Hydra, Greece. As we strolled along the coastline, we encountered two older friends on a similar journey. It was then that I noticed a touching moment – our shadows cast upon them as they passed by. It felt almost poetic, as if these intersecting shadows projected a path, a glimpse into the future.. something.
